#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/gentoo-x86+raid+lvm2-quickinstall.xml:152
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"On the one hand, if you want extra stability, consider using raid-1 (or even\n"
"raid-5) for your swap partition(s) so that a drive failure would not corrupt\n"
"your swap space and crash applications that are using it. On the other hand, if\n"
"you want extra performance, just let the kernel use distinct swap partitions as\n"
"it does striping by default.\n"
msgstr ""

